# Design Token Rules

## Token Import
Always import tokens from the central tokens index. Never import from individual token files directly.

```ts
// CORRECT
import { useTokens } from '@/tokens';
import { typography } from '@/tokens';

// WRONG
import { brand } from '@/tokens/brand';
import { alias } from '@/tokens/alias';
```

## Theme-Aware Components
All components must accept a `theme` prop defaulting to `'light'` and use `useTokens()` to resolve mapped tokens.

```tsx
// CORRECT
import { useTokens } from '@/tokens';
import type { Theme } from '@/tokens';

interface Props {
  theme?: Theme;
}

const MyComponent = ({ theme = 'light' }: Props) => {
  const t = useTokens(theme);
  return <div style={{ backgroundColor: t.surface.primary.default }} />;
};

// WRONG
const MyComponent = () => (
  <div style={{ backgroundColor: '#4A4DE8' }} />
);
```

## Colors
Never use hard-coded hex values, rgb(), rgba(), or CSS color names. Always use mapped tokens.

```tsx
// CORRECT
color: t.text.default.body
backgroundColor: t.surface.primary.defaultSubtle
borderColor: t.border.primary.default

// WRONG
color: '#181819'
backgroundColor: '#EDEDFD'
borderColor: 'purple'
```

### Color token namespaces
- `t.surface.*` — background colors for containers, buttons, badges
- `t.text.*` — text colors (heading, body, caption, placeholder, on-color)
- `t.icon.*` — icon fill colors
- `t.border.*` — border and outline colors
- `t.base` / `t.default` — page-level background colors

### Interaction states
Always use the correct state variant — never manually lighten or darken colors.

```tsx
// CORRECT
onMouseEnter={() => setColor(t.surface.primary.defaultHover)}

// WRONG
onMouseEnter={() => setColor('#3B3EBA')}
```

## Spacing
Never use hard-coded pixel values for padding, margin, gap, or dimensions. Use `t.layoutSpacing.*` for component spacing.

```tsx
// CORRECT
padding: `${t.layoutSpacing.md}px`     // 24px
gap: `${t.layoutSpacing.sm}px`         // 16px
margin: `${t.layoutSpacing.xsm}px`     // 8px

// WRONG
padding: '24px'
gap: 16
margin: '0.5rem'
```

### Layout spacing scale reference
| Token         | Value |
|---------------|-------|
| none          | 0px   |
| 2xsm          | 4px   |
| xsm           | 8px   |
| sm            | 16px  |
| md            | 24px  |
| lg            | 32px  |
| xlg           | 40px  |
| 2xlg          | 48px  |

## Border Radius
Always use `t.borderRadius.*` tokens. Never hard-code border radius values.

```tsx
// CORRECT
borderRadius: `${t.borderRadius[200]}px`   // 8px  — inputs, cards
borderRadius: `${t.borderRadius[400]}px`   // 16px — modals
borderRadius: `${t.borderRadius.round}px`  // pill — badges, chips

// WRONG
borderRadius: '8px'
borderRadius: 9999
```

## Border Width
Always use `t.borderWidth.*` tokens.

```tsx
// CORRECT
borderWidth: `${t.borderWidth.sm}px`   // 2px — default borders
borderWidth: `${t.borderWidth.xs}px`   // 1px — subtle dividers

// WRONG
borderWidth: '1px'
border: '2px solid purple'
```

## Typography
Never hard-code font sizes, font weights, line heights, or font families.

### For static text styles use the `typography` export:
```tsx
import { typography } from '@/tokens';

// CORRECT
style={{
  fontSize: `${typography.body.md.fontSize}px`,
  fontFamily: typography.body.md.fontFamily,
  fontWeight: typography.body.md.fontWeight,
  lineHeight: `${typography.body.md.lineHeight}px`,
}}

// WRONG
style={{
  fontSize: '16px',
  fontFamily: 'Rubik, sans-serif',
  fontWeight: 600,
  lineHeight: '20px',
}}
```

### Typography style reference
**Body:** `typography.body.sm` | `body.md` | `body.lg`
**Body variants:** append `Link` or `Semibold` (e.g. `typography.body.mdSemibold`)
**Headings:** `typography.heading.h1` through `typography.heading.h6`
**Labels:** `typography.label.primary` | `typography.label.secondary`

### Font family
Always use `'Rubik'` — never substitute with system fonts or other families.

## Responsive Typography
For components that need to respond to viewport size, use `responsive` tokens.

```tsx
import { responsive } from '@/tokens';

// Desktop heading size
fontSize: `${responsive.font.desktop.headings.h1.fontSize}px`

// Mobile heading size  
fontSize: `${responsive.font.mobile.headings.h1.fontSize}px`
```

## Disabled States
Always use disabled-specific tokens — never use opacity to fake a disabled appearance.

```tsx
// CORRECT
style={{
  backgroundColor: t.surface.disabled.default,
  color: t.text.disabled.default,
  borderColor: t.border.disabled.default,
  cursor: 'not-allowed',
}}

// WRONG
style={{ opacity: 0.4 }}
```

## Token Layer Rules
The token system has three layers. Components must only use the mapped layer.

| Layer      | File         | Used by          |
|------------|--------------|------------------|
| brand.ts   | Raw values   | alias.ts only    |
| alias.ts   | Semantic     | mapped.ts only   |
| mapped.ts  | Use-case     | Components ✅     |

Never reference `brand.*` or `alias.*` directly in component files.

## New Component Checklist
Before submitting any new component, verify:
- [ ] Imports tokens from `@/tokens` only
- [ ] Accepts `theme?: Theme` prop
- [ ] Uses `useTokens(theme)` for all color, spacing, border values
- [ ] Uses `typography.*` for all font properties
- [ ] No hard-coded hex values, pixel values, or font strings anywhere
- [ ] Hover/focus/disabled states use correct token variants
